d. However, $\\zeta$ at small scales ($r_\\parallel<1$pMpc) and\nb-dependence of $\\zeta$ in simulations are found inconsistent with the\nobservations. This could either be related to the fact that none of these\nsimulations reproduce the observed b-distribution and $N_{HI}$ distribution for\n$N_{HI}>10^{14}$cm$^{-2}$ self-consistently or to the widespread of\nsignal-to-noise ratio in the observed data.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 10 Dec 2020 19:00:07 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 13 Jul 2021 11:15:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-11-24"}
