tion requires additional knowledge and, in\nthis work, HD provides the additional constraint to derive the gas mass and\nsupports the inference of CO depletion in the TW Hya disk. Our final thermal\nstructure confirms the use of HD as a powerful probe of protoplanetary disk\nmass. Additionally, the method laid out in this paper is an employable strategy\nfor extraction of disk temperatures and masses in the future.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 10 Dec 2020 19:00:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-02-17"}
