ion of\nmagnetic field strength on PNS effects. We find that thresholds are higher in\nan approximately linearly inhomogeneous field (relevant to MRI) than in a\nrather homogeneous distribution (as in MPI). Finally, given the large\nintersubject variability of PNS sensitivity, we propose employing a versatile\nlow-cost system (such as presented here) for fast offline determination of a\nsubject's limits prior to medical scanning, and then using this information to\nboost clinical imaging while preserving the patient's safety.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 11 Dec 2020 10:40:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-04-11"}
